Production-ready.\n\n## Overview\n\nbeads_zig (`bz`) is a command-line issue tracker that lives in your git repository. No accounts, no internet required, no external dependencies. Your issues stay with your code.\n\n```\n.beads/\n  issues.jsonl    # Main storage - git-friendly, human-readable\n  issues.wal      # Write-ahead log for concurrent writes\n  .beads.lock     # Lock file for process coordination\n  config.yaml     # Project configuration\n```\n\n## Features\n\n- **Pure Zig**: No C dependencies, single static binary\n- **Local-first**: All data lives in `.beads/` within your repo\n- **Offline**: Works without internet connectivity\n- **Git-friendly**: JSONL format for clean version control diffs\n- **Cross-platform**: Compiles to Linux, macOS, Windows, ARM64\n- **Non-invasive**: Never modifies source code or runs git commands automatically\n- **Agent-first**: Machine-readable JSON/TOON output for AI tooling integration\n- **Concurrent-safe**: Lock + WAL architecture handles parallel agent writes without contention\n\n### Issue Management\n\n- Priority levels (0=critical through 4=backlog)\n- Status tracking (open, in_progress, blocked, deferred, closed, tombstone)\n- Dependency tracking with automatic cycle detection\n- Labels and type classification (bug/feature/task/epic/chore/docs/question)\n- Assignees and owners\n- Deferral with date-based scheduling\n- Full audit trail (history command)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- **[rich_zig](https://github.com/hotschmoe-zig/rich_zig)** v1.1.1 - Terminal formatting (colors, TTY detection)\n- **[toon_zig](https://github.com/hotschmoe-zig/toon_zig)** v0.1.5 - LLM-optimized output format\n\nNo C dependencies. No SQLite. Pure Zig.\n\n## Building\n\nRequires Zig 0.15.2 or later.\n\n```bash\n# Build\nzig build\n\n# Run\nzig build run\n\n# Run with arguments\nzig build run -- <args>\n\n# Run tests\nzig test src/root.zig\n\n# Format source\nzig build fmt\n\n# Cross-compile\nzig build -Dtarget=aarch64-linux-gnu      # Linux ARM64\nzig build -Dtarget=x86_64-windows-gnu     # Windows\nzig build -Dtarget=aarch64-macos          # macOS Apple Silicon\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```bash\n# Initialize beads in current repo\nbz init\n\n# Create an issue\nbz create \"Fix login bug\" --type bug --priority 1\n\n# Quick capture (print ID only)\nbz q \"Todo item\"\n\n# List issues\nbz list\nbz list --status open --priority 1\n\n# Show issue details\nbz show <id>\n\n# Update issue\nbz update <id> --status in_progress --assignee alice\n\n# Close/reopen\nbz close <id> --reason \"Fixed in commit abc123\"\nbz reopen <id>\n\n# Dependencies\nbz dep add <child-id> <blocker-id>\nbz dep list <id>\nbz ready          # Show unblocked issues\nbz blocked        # Show blocked issues\n\n# Labels\nbz label add <id> urgent backend\nbz label list <id>\n\n# Comments\nbz comments add <id> \"Investigation notes...\"\nbz comments list <id>\n\n# Defer until later\nbz defer <id> --until 2024-02-15\nbz defer <id> --until +7d    # Relative date\n\n# Search\nbz search \"login\"\n\n# Dependency graph\nbz graph --format dot > deps.dot\n\n# JSON output for scripting/AI agents\nbz list --json\nbz show <id> --toon    # LLM-optimized format\n```\n\n## Commands\n\n**Workspace**: `init`, `info`, `stats`, `doctor`, `config`\n\n**Issue CRUD**: `create` (add, new), `q` (quick), `show` (get, view), `update` (edit), `close` (done), `reopen`, `delete` (rm)\n\n**Queries**: `list` (ls), `ready`, `blocked`, `search` (find), `stale`, `count`\n\n**Dependencies**: `dep add`, `dep remove`, `dep list`, `dep tree`, `dep cycles`, `graph`\n\n**Labels**: `label add`, `label remove`, `label list`, `label list-all`\n\n**Comments**: `comments add`, `comments list`\n\n**Scheduling**: `defer`, `undefer`\n\n**Audit**: `history` (log), `audit`\n\n**Sync**: `sync` (flush, export) with `--flush-only` and `--import-only`\n\n**System**: `version`, `schema`, `completions`, `help`\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nsrc/\n  main.zig           # CLI entry point\n  root.zig           # Library exports\n  cli/               # 26 command implementations\n    args.zig         # Argument parsing (34 commands + subcommands)\n    common.zig       # Shared context and output helpers\n  storage/\n    jsonl.zig        # JSONL file I/O (atomic writes)\n    store.zig        # In-memory IssueStore with indexing\n    graph.zig        # Dependency graph with cycle detection\n    lock.zig         # flock-based concurrent write locking\n    wal.zig          # Write-ahead log operations\n    compact.zig      # WAL compaction into main file\n  models/            # Data structures (Issue, Status, Priority, etc.)\n  id/                # Hash-based ID generation (base36)\n  config/            # YAML configuration\n  output/            # Formatting (plain, rich, json, toon, quiet)\n  errors.zig         # Structured error handling\n```\n\n**Storage** (Lock + WAL + Compact):\n```\n.beads/\n  issues.jsonl      # Main file (compacted state, git-tracked)\n  issues.wal        # Write-ahead log (gitignored)\n  .beads.lock       # Lock file for flock (gitignored)\n```\n\n- **Writes**: Acquire flock -> append to WAL -> fsync -> release (~1ms)\n- **Reads**: Load main + replay WAL in memory (lock-free)\n- **Compaction**: Merge WAL into main when threshold exceeded (100 entries or 100KB)\n- Crash-safe: flock auto-releases on process termination, atomic file operations\n\n**Design principles**:\n- Explicit over implicit (no background daemons)\n- User-triggered operations only\n- Rich terminal output with TTY detection\n- Hash-based IDs prevent merge conflicts\n\n## Global Options\n\n```\n--json              Machine-readable JSON output\n--toon              LLM-optimized TOON format\n-q, --quiet         Suppress non-essential output\n-v, --verbose       Increase verbosity (-vv for debug)\n--no-color          Disable ANSI colors (respects NO_COLOR env)\n--data <path>       Override .beads/ directory\n--actor <name>      Set actor for audit trail\n--lock-timeout <ms> Lock timeout (default 5000)\n--no-auto-flush     Skip automatic WAL flush\n--no-auto-import    Skip automatic import on read\n```\n\n## Why Zig?\n\n- Single static binary with no runtime dependencies\n- Compiles to native code for all major platforms\n- No C dependencies - pure Zig implementation\n- Memory safety without garbage collection\n- Fast compilation (~2-5s debug builds)\n\n## Inspiration\n\n- Original [beads](https://github.com/steveyegge/beads) by Steve Yegge\n- [beads_rust](https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/beads_rust) by Jeffrey Emanuel\n\n## License\n\nMIT License - see [LICENSE](LICENSE)\n","numLines":223,"startLine":1,"totalLines":223}}}

722→---\n   723→\n   724→## Appendix B: Data Format\n   725→\n   726→### JSONL Format\n   727→\n   728→beads_zig uses JSONL (JSON Lines) as its storage format:\n   729→\n   730→```json\n   731→{\"id\":\"bd-abc123\",\"title\":\"Fix login bug\",\"description\":null,\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"assignee\":\"alice\",\"created_at\":\"2024-01-29T15:30:00Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2024-01-29T15:30:00Z\"}\n   732→```\n   733→\n   734→Key requirements:\n   735→- One JSON object per line\n   736→- RFC3339 timestamps\n   737→- Null for missing optional fields\n   738→- UTF-8 encoding\n   739→\n   740→### Storage Architecture\n   741→\n   742→beads_zig uses Lock + WAL + Compact (no SQLite):\n   743→\n   744→```\n   745→.beads/\n   746→  issues.jsonl    # Main file (compacted state, git-tracked)\n   747→  issues.wal      # Write-ahead log (gitignored)\n   748→  .beads.lock     # flock target (gitignored)\n   749→```\n   750→\n   751→**Architecture comparison (for reference):**\n   752→| Aspect | SQLite approach | beads_zig |\n   753→|--------|-----------------|-----------|\n   754→| Storage | SQLite + WAL mode | JSONL + custom WAL |\n   755→| Concurrency | SQLite locking | flock + append WAL |\n   756→| Binary size | ~5-8MB | ~12KB |\n   757→| Write time | Variable (lock contention) | Constant ~1ms |\n   758→| Read time | O(1) with indexes | O(n) linear scan |\n   759→\n   760→**Trade-offs:**\n   761→- beads_zig sacrifices read performance (linear scan vs indexes)\n   762→- beads_zig gains concurrent write performance (no lock contention)\n   763→- For typical workloads (<10k issues), linear scan is fast enough\n   764→\n   765→---\n   766→\n   767→## Appendix C: Priority Order\n   768→\n   769→Recommended implementation order for efficient development:\n   770→\n allocations\n\n### Cross-Platform (bd-kl5 - DONE)\n\n- [x] Linux support\n- [x] macOS support\n- [x] Windows support\n- [x] Path handling (std.fs.path)\n\n---\n\n## Appendix A: CLI Command Reference\n\nTarget command set for beads_zig (inspired by beads_rust):\n\n```\nCOMMANDS:\n  init           Initialize workspace\n  create         Create new issue\n  q              Quick capture (create + print ID)\n  show           Display issue details\n  update         Update issue fields\n  close          Close issue\n  reopen         Reopen closed issue\n  delete         Soft delete (tombstone)\n  list           List issues with filters\n  ready          Show actionable issues\n  blocked        Show blocked issues\n  search         Full-text search\n  stale          Find stale issues\n  count          Count issues\n  dep            Dependency management\n    add          Add dependency\n    remove       Remove dependency\n    list         List dependencies\n    tree         Show dependency tree\n    cycles       Detect cycles\n  label          Label management\n    add          Add labels\n    remove       Remove labels\n    list         List labels on issue\n    list-all     List all labels\n  comments       Comment management\n    add          Add comment\n    list         List comments\n  history        Show issue history\n  audit          Deep audit analysis\n  epic           Epic management\n  defer          Defer issue\n  undefer        Remove deferral\n  orphans        Find orphaned issues\n  changelog      Generate changelog\n  lint           Validate data integrity\n  graph          Dependency graph\n  sync           Save/load JSONL\n  doctor         Run diagnostics\n  stats/status   Project statistics\n  info           Workspace info\n  config         Configuration\n  agents         Manage agent instructions\n  version        Show version\n  completions    Shell completions\n```\n\n---\n\n## Appendix B: Data Format\n\n### JSONL Format\n\nbeads_zig uses JSONL (JSON Lines) as its storage format:\n\n```json\n{\"id\":\"bd-abc123\",\"title\":\"Fix login bug\",\"description\":null,\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"assignee\":\"alice\",\"created_at\":\"2024-01-29T15:30:00Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2024-01-29T15:30:00Z\"}\n```\n\nKey requirements:\n- One JSON object per line\n- RFC3339 timestamps\n- Null for missing optional fields\n- UTF-8 encoding\n\n### Storage Architecture\n\nbeads_zig uses Lock + WAL + Compact (no SQLite):\n\n```\n.beads/\n  issues.jsonl    # Main file (compacted state, git-tracked)\n  issues.wal      # Write-ahead log (gitignored)\n  .beads.lock     # flock target (gitignored)\n```\n\n**Architecture comparison (for reference):**\n| Aspect | SQLite approach | beads_zig |\n|--------|-----------------|-----------|\n| Storage | SQLite + WAL mode | JSONL + custom WAL |\n| Concurrency | SQLite locking | flock + append WAL |\n| Binary size | ~5-8MB | ~12KB |\n| Write time | Variable (lock contention) | Constant ~1ms |\n| Read time | O(1) with indexes | O(n) linear scan |\n\n**Trade-offs:**\n- beads_zig sacrifices read performance (linear scan vs indexes)\n- beads_zig gains concurrent write performance (no lock contention)\n- For typical workloads (<10k issues), linear scan is fast enough\n\n---\n\n## Appendix C: Priority Order\n\nRecommended implementation order for efficient development:\n\n1. **Models** - Foundation for everything [DONE]\n2. ParseError,\n    OutOfMemory,\n    ReplayPartialFailure,\n};\n\n/// Statistics from WAL replay operations.\npub const ReplayStats = struct {\n    applied: usize = 0,\n    skipped: usize = 0,\n    failed: usize = 0,\n    failure_ids: []const []const u8 = &.{},\n\n    pub fn deinit(self: *ReplayStats, allocator: std.mem.Allocator) void {\n        for (self.failure_ids) |id| {\n            allocator.free(id);\n        }\n        if (self.failure_ids.len > 0) {\n            allocator.free(self.failure_ids);\n        }\n    }\n\n    pub fn hasFailures(self: ReplayStats) bool {\n        return self.failed > 0;\n    }\n};\n\n/// WAL operation types.\npub const WalOp = enum {\n    add,\n    update,\n    close,\n    reopen,\n    delete,\n    set_blocked,\n    unset_blocked,\n\n    pub fn toString(self: WalOp) []const u8 {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .add => \"add\",\n            .update => \"update\",\n            .close => \"close\",\n            .reopen => \"reopen\",\n            .delete => \"delete\",\n            .set_blocked => \"set_blocked\",\n            .unset_blocked => \"unset_blocked\",\n        };\n    }\n\n    pub fn fromString(s: []const u8) ?WalOp {\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"add\")) return .add;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"update\")) return .update;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"close\")) return .close;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"reopen\")) return .reopen;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"delete\")) return .delete;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"set_blocked\")) return .set_blocked;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"unset_blocked\")) return .unset_blocked;\n        return null;\n    }\n};\n\n/// A single WAL entry representing one operation.\npub const WalEntry = struct {\n    op: WalOp,\n    ts: i64, // Unix timestamp for ordering\n    id: []const u8, // Issue ID\n    data: ?Issue, // Full issue for add/update, null for status-only ops\n\n    const Self = @This();\n\n    /// Custom JSON serialization for WalEntry.\n    pub fn jsonStringify(self: Self, jws: anytype) !void {\n        try jws.beginObject();\n\n        try jws.objectField(\"op\");\n        try jws.write(self.op.toString());\n\n        try jws.objectField(\"ts\");\n        try jws.write(self.ts);\n\n        try jws.objectField(\"id\");\n        try jws.write(self.id);\n\n        try jws.objectField(\"data\");\n        if (self.data) |issue| {\n            try jws.write(issue);\n        } else {\n            try jws.write(null);\n        }\n\n        try jws.endObject();\n    }\n};\n\n/// Parsed WAL entry for replay.\npub const ParsedWalEntry = struct {\n    op: WalOp,\n    ts: i64,\n    id: []const u8,\n    data: ?Issue,\n\n    pub fn deinit(self: *ParsedWalEntry, allocator: std.mem.Allocator) void {\n        allocator.free(self.id);\n        if (self.data) |*issue| {\n            var i = issue.*;\n            i.deinit(allocator);\n        }\n    }\n};\n\n/// WAL file manager for reading and writing operations.\npub const Wal = struct {\n    wal_path: []const u8,\n    lock_path: []const u8,\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n\n    const Self = @This();\n\n    pub fn init(beads_dir: []const u8, allocator: std.mem.Allocator) !Self {\n        const wal_path = try std.fs.path.join(allocator, &.{ beads_dir, \"beads.wal\" });\n        errdefer allocator.free(wal_path);\n\n        const lock_path = try std.fs.path.join(allocator, &.{ beads_dir, \"beads.lock\" });\n\n        return Self{\n            .wal_path = wal_path,\n            .lock_path = lock_path,\n            .allocator = allocator,\n        };\n    }\n\n    pub fn deinit(self: *Self) void {\n        self.allocator.free(self.wal_path);\n        self.allocator.free(self.lock_path);\n    }\n\n    /// Append an entry to the WAL under exclusive lock.\n    /// Ensures durability via fsync before releasing lock.\n    pub fn appendEntry(self: *Self, entry: WalEntry) !void {\n        var lock = BeadsLock.acquire(self.lock_path) catch return WalError.LockFailed;\n        defer lock.release();\n\n        try self.appendEntryUnlocked(entry);\n    }\n\n    /// Append entry without acquiring lock (caller must hold lock).\n    fn appendEntryUnlocked(self: *Self, entry: WalEntry) !void {\n        const dir = fs.cwd();\n\n        // Ensure parent directory exists\n        if (std.fs.path.dirname(self.wal_path)) |parent| {\n            dir.makePath(parent) catch |err| switch (err) {\n                error.PathAlreadyExists => {},\n                else => return err,\n            };\n        }\n\n        // Open or create WAL file in append mode\n        const file = dir.createFile(self.wal_path, .{\n            .truncate = false,\n        }) catch return WalError.WriteError;\n        defer file.close();\n\n        // Seek to end\n        file.seekFromEnd(0) catch return WalError.WriteError;\n\n        // Serialize entry\n        const json_bytes = std.json.Stringify.valueAlloc(self.allocator, entry, .{}) catch return WalError.WriteError;\n        defer self.allocator.free(json_bytes);\n\n        // Write entry + newline\n        file.writeAll(json_bytes) catch return WalError.WriteError;\n        file.writeAll(\"\\n\") catch return WalError.WriteError;\n\n        // fsync for durability\n        file.sync() catch return WalError.WriteError;\n    }\n\n    /// Read all WAL entries.\n    pub fn readEntries(self: *Self) ![]ParsedWalEntry {\n        const file = fs.cwd().openFile(self.wal_path, .{}) catch |err| switch (err) {\n            error.FileNotFound => return &[_]ParsedWalEntry{},\n            else => return err,\n        };\n        defer file.close();\n\n        const content = file.readToEndAlloc(self.allocator, 100 * 1024 * 1024) catch return WalError.ParseError;\n        defer self.allocator.free(content);\n\n        var entries: std.ArrayListUnmanaged(ParsedWalEntry) = .{};\n        errdefer {\n            for (entries.items) |*e| {\n                e.deinit(self.allocator);\n            }\n            entries.deinit(self.allocator);\n        }\n\n        var line_start: usize = 0;\n        for (content, 0..) |c, i| {\n            if (c == '\\n') {\n                const line = content[line_start..i];\n                line_start = i + 1;\n\n                if (line.len == 0) continue;\n\n                if (self.parseEntry(line)) |entry| {\n                    try entries.append(self.allocator, entry);\n                } else |_| {\n                    // Skip malformed entries (graceful degradation)\n                    continue;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        // Handle last line if no trailing newline\n        if (line_start < content.len) {\n            const line = content[line_start..];\n            if (line.len > 0) {\n                if (self.parseEntry(line)) |entry| {\n                    try entries.append(self.allocator, entry);\n                } else |_| {}\n            }\n        }\n\n        return entries.toOwnedSlice(self.allocator);\n    }\n\n    /// Parse a single WAL entry line.\n    fn parseEntry(self: *Self, line: []const u8) !ParsedWalEntry {\n        const parsed = std.json.parseFromSlice(\n            struct {\n                op: []const u8,\n                ts: i64,\n                id: []const u8,\n                data: ?Issue,\n            },\n            self.allocator,\n            line,\n            .{ .ignore_unknown_fields = true, .allocate = .alloc_always },\n        ) catch return WalError.ParseError;\n        defer parsed.deinit();\n\n        const op = WalOp.fromString(parsed.value.op) orelse return WalError.InvalidOperation;\n\n        // Clone strings since parsed will be freed\n        const id = try self.allocator.dupe(u8, parsed.value.id);\n        errdefer self.allocator.free(id);\n\n        var data: ?Issue = null;\n        if (parsed.value.data) |issue| {\n            data = try issue.clone(self.allocator);\n        }\n\n        return ParsedWalEntry{\n            .op = op,\n            .ts = parsed.value.ts,\n            .id = id,\n            .data = data,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Replay WAL entries onto an IssueStore.\n    /// Applies operations in timestamp order.\n    /// Returns statistics about the replay through the slice pointer)\n        std.mem.sortUnstable(ParsedWalEntry, @constCast(entries), {}, struct {\n            fn lessThan(_: void, a: ParsedWalEntry, b: ParsedWalEntry) bool {\n       errdefer {\n            for (failure_ids.items) |id| {\n                self.allocator.free(id);\n            }\n            failure_ids.deinit(self.allocator);\n        }\n\n        // Apply stats.failure_ids = failure_ids.toOwnedSlice(self.allocator) catch &.{};\n        return stats;\n    }\n\n    /// Result of applying a single WAL entry.\n    const ApplyResult = enum {\n Event struct and EventType enum for the audit log system.\n//!\n//! Events track changes to issues for audit and history purposes.\n//! Each event records who made a change, what changed, and when.\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\nconst Status = @import(\"status.zig\").Status;\nconst Priority = @import(\"priority.zig\").Priority;\n\n/// Types of events that can occur on an issue.\npub const EventType = enum {\n    created,\n    updated,\n    status_changed,\n    priority_changed,\n    assignee_changed,\n    commented,\n    closed,\n    reopened,\n    dependency_added,\n    dependency_removed,\n    label_added,\n    label_removed,\n    compacted,\n    deleted,\n    restored,\n\n    const Self = @This();\n\n    /// Convert EventType to its string representation.\n    pub fn toString(self: Self) []const u8 {\n        return @tagName(self);\n    }\n\n    /// Parse a string into an EventType.\n    /// Returns null for unknown values.\n    pub fn fromString(s: []const u8) ?Self {\n        return std.meta.stringToEnum(Self, s);\n    }\n\n    /// JSON serialization for std.json.\n    pub fn jsonStringify(self: Self, jws: anytype) !void {\n        try jws.write(self.toString());\n    }\n\n    /// JSON deserialization for std.json.\n    pub fn jsonParse(allocator: std.mem.Allocator, source: anytype, options: std.json.ParseOptions) !Self {\n        const token = try source.nextAllocMax(allocator, .alloc_if_needed, options.max_value_len.?);\n        const str = switch (token) {\n            .string, .allocated_string => |s| s,\n            else => return error.UnexpectedToken,\n        };\n        return fromString(str) orelse error.UnexpectedToken;\n    }\n\n    /// JSON deserialization from already-parsed value.\n    pub fn jsonParseFromValue(allocator: std.mem.Allocator, source: std.json.Value, options: std.json.ParseOptions) !Self {\n        _ = allocator;\n        _ = options;\n        return switch (source) {\n            .string => |s| fromString(s) orelse error.UnexpectedToken,\n            else => error.UnexpectedToken,\n        };\n    }\n};\n\n/// Validation errors for Event.\npub const EventError = error{\n    EmptyActor,\n    EmptyIssueId,\n};\n\n/// An audit log entry for an issue change.\npub const Event = struct {\n    id: i64, // Unique identifier, 0 for new events before insert\n    issue_id: []const u8, // The issue this event relates to\n    event_type: EventType, // What kind of change occurred\n    actor: []const u8, // Who performed the action\n    old_value: ?[]const u8, // JSON of previous state (null for creation)\n    new_value: ?[]const u8, // JSON of new state (null for deletion)\n    created_at: i64, candidate)) {\n        score += 80;\n    }\n\n    // Common prefix length\n    var common_prefix: usize = 0;\n    const min_len = @min(target.len, candidate.len);\n    for (0..min_len) |i| {\n        if (target[i] == candidate[i]) {\n            common_prefix += 1;\n        } else {\n            break;\n        }\n    }\n    score += @intCast(common_prefix * 5);\n\n    // Contains target as substring\n    if (std.mem.indexOf(u8, candidate, target) != null) {\n        score += 30;\n    }\n\n    // Similar length bonus\n    const len_diff: i32 = @intCast(@abs(@as(i64, @intCast(target.len)) Compaction flow:\n//! 1. Acquire BeadsLock (exclusive)\n//! 2. Load beads.jsonl into memory\n//! 3. Replay beads.wal operations\n//! 4. Write merged state to beads.jsonl.tmp\n//! 5. fsync for durability\n//! 6. Atomic rename over beads.jsonl\n//! 7. Truncate beads.wal\n//! 8. Release lock\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\nconst fs = std.fs;\nconst BeadsLock = @import(\"lock.zig\").BeadsLock;\nconst Wal = @import(\"wal.zig\").Wal;\nconst JsonlFile = @import(\"jsonl.zig\").JsonlFile;\nconst IssueStore = @import(\"store.zig\").IssueStore;\nconst test_util = @import(\"../test_util.zig\");\n\npub const CompactError = error{\n    LockFailed,\n    CompactionFailed,\n    WriteError,\n    AtomicRenameFailed,\n    OutOfMemory,\n};\n\n/// Thresholds for automatic compaction.\npub const CompactionThresholds = struct {\n    /// Maximum number of WAL entries before compaction.\n    max_entries: usize = 100,\n    /// Maximum WAL file size in bytes before compaction.\n    max_bytes: u64 = 100 * 1024, // 100KB\n};\n\n/// Statistics about the WAL for monitoring.\npub const WalStats = struct {\n    entry_count: usize,\n    file_size: u64,\n    needs_compaction: bool,\n};\n\n/// Compactor handles WAL compaction operations.\npub const Compactor = struct {\n    beads_dir: []const u8,\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n    thresholds: CompactionThresholds,\n\n    const Self = @This();\n\n    pub fn init(beads_dir: []const u8, allocator: std.mem.Allocator) Self {\n        return .{\n            .beads_dir = beads_dir,\n            .allocator = allocator,\n            .thresholds = .{},\n        };\n    }\n\n    pub fn initWithThresholds(beads_dir: []const u8, allocator: std.mem.Allocator, thresholds: CompactionThresholds) Self {\n        return .{\n            .beads_dir = beads_dir,\n            .allocator = allocator,\n            .thresholds = thresholds,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Get current WAL statistics.\n    pub fn walStats(self: *Self) !WalStats {\n        var wal = try Wal.init(self.beads_dir, self.allocator);\n        defer wal.deinit();\n\n        const entry_count = try wal.entryCount();\n        const file_size = try wal.fileSize();\n\n        return .{\n            .entry_count = entry_count,\n            .file_size = file_size,\n            .needs_compaction = entry_count >= self.thresholds.max_entries or\n                file_size >= self.thresholds.max_bytes,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Trigger compaction if WAL exceeds threshold.\n    /// Returns true if compaction was performed.\n    pub fn maybeCompact(self: *Self) !bool {\n        const stats = try self.walStats();\n        if (stats.needs_compaction) {\n            try self.compact();\n            return true;\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    /// Compact WAL into main file.\n    /// 1. Acquire BeadsLock\n    /// 2. Load beads.jsonl into memory\n    /// 3. Replay beads.wal operations\n    /// 4. Write merged state to beads.jsonl.tmp\n    /// 5. fsync for durability\n    /// 6. Atomic rename over beads.jsonl\n    /// 7. Truncate beads.wal\n    /// 8. Release lock\n    pub fn compact(self: *Self) !void {\n        const lock_path = try std.fs.path.join(self.allocator, &.{ self.beads_dir, \"beads.lock\" });\n        defer self.allocator.free(lock_path);\n\n        const jsonl_path = try std.fs.path.join(self.allocator, &.{ self.beads_dir, \"beads.jsonl\" });\n        defer self.allocator.free(jsonl_path);\n\n        // 1. Acquire exclusive lock\n        var lock = BeadsLock.acquire(lock_path) catch return CompactError.LockFailed;\n        defer lock.release();\n\n        // 2. Load main file into memory\n        var store = IssueStore.init(self.allocator, jsonl_path);\n        defer store.deinit();\n\n        store.loadFromFile() catch |err| switch (err) {\n            error.FileNotFound => {}, // Empty main file is OK\n            else => return CompactError.CompactionFailed,\n        };\n\n        // 3. Replay WAL operations\n        var wal = try Wal.init(self.beads_dir, self.allocator);\n        defer wal.deinit();\n\n        var replay_stats = wal.replay(&store) catch return CompactError.CompactionFailed;\n        defer replay_stats.deinit(self.allocator);\n        // Note: During compaction we proceed even if some replays failed,\n        // since the remaining operations should still be compacted.\n\n        // 4-6. Write merged state atomically\n        try self.writeAtomically(jsonl_path, store.issues.items);\n\n        // 7. Truncate WAL\n        wal.truncate() catch return CompactError.CompactionFailed;\n    }\n\n    /// Write issues to file atomically (temp file + fsync + rename).\n    fn writeAtomically(self: *Self, target_path: []const u8, issues: []const @import(\"../models/issue.zig\").Issue) !void {\n        const dir = fs.cwd();\n\n        // Create temp file path\n        var tmp_path_buf: [std.fs.max_path_bytes]u8 = undefined;\n        const tmp_path = std.fmt.bufPrint(&tmp_path_buf, \"{s}.tmp.{d}\", .{\n            target_path,\n            std.time.milliTimestamp(),\n        }) catch return CompactError.WriteError;\n\n        // Write to temp file\n        const tmp_file = dir.createFile(tmp_path, .{}) catch return CompactError.WriteError;\n        errdefer {\n            tmp_file.close();\n            dir.deleteFile(tmp_path) catch {};\n        }\n\n        // Serialize and write each issue\n        for (issues) |issue| {\n            const json_bytes = std.json.Stringify.valueAlloc(self.allocator, issue, .{}) catch return CompactError.WriteError;\n            defer self.allocator.free(json_bytes);\n\n            tmp_file.writeAll(json_bytes) catch return CompactError.WriteError;\n            tmp_file.writeAll(\"\\n\") catch return CompactError.WriteError;\n        }\n\n        // 5. fsync for durability\n        tmp_file.sync() catch return CompactError.WriteError;\n        tmp_file.close();\n\n        // 6. Atomic rename\n        dir.rename(tmp_path, target_path) catch return CompactError.AtomicRenameFailed;\n    }\n\n    /// Force compaction regardless of thresholds.\n    /// Use this for explicit sync operations.\n    pub fn forceCompact(self: *Self) !void {\n        try self.compact();\n    }\n};\n\n// --- Tests ---\n\ntest \"Compactor.init\" {\n    const allocator = std.testing.allocator;\n\n Common CLI utilities shared across commands.\n//!\n//! Provides workspace loading, error handling, and shared result types\n//! to reduce duplication across command implementations.\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\nconst storage = @import(\"../storage/mod.zig\");\nconst output_mod = @import(\"../output/mod.zig\");\nconst args = @import(\"args.zig\");\n\npub const Output = output_mod.Output;\npub const OutputOptions = output_mod.OutputOptions;\npub const IssueStore = storage.IssueStore;\npub const DependencyGraph = storage.DependencyGraph;\n\n/// Common errors shared across CLI commands.\npub const CommandError = error{\n    WorkspaceNotInitialized,\n    StorageError,\n    OutOfMemory,\n};\n\n/// Context for executing a CLI command with an initialized workspace.\npub const CommandContext = struct {\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n    output: Output,\n    store: IssueStore,\n    issues_path: []const u8,\n    global: args.GlobalOptions,\n\n    /// Initialize a command context by loading the workspace.\n    /// Returns null and outputs an error if workspace is not initialized.\n    pub fn init(\n        allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n        global: args.GlobalOptions,\n    ) CommandError!?CommandContext {\n        var output = Output.init(allocator, .{\n            .json = global.json,\n            .toon = global.toon,\n            .quiet = global.quiet,\n            .silent = global.silent,\n            .no_color = global.no_color,\n        });\n\n        const beads_dir = global.data_path orelse \".beads\";\n        const issues_path = std.fs.path.join(allocator, &.{ beads_dir, \"issues.jsonl\" }) catch {\n            return CommandError.OutOfMemory;\n        };\n\n        std.fs.cwd().access(issues_path, .{}) catch |err| {\n            if (err == error.FileNotFound) {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"workspace not initialized. Run 'bz init' first.\") catch {};\n                allocator.free(issues_path);\n                return null;\n            }\n            outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"cannot access workspace\") catch {};\n            allocator.free(issues_path);\n            return CommandError.StorageError;\n        };\n\n        var store = IssueStore.init(allocator, issues_path);\n\n        store.loadFromFile() catch |err| {\n            if (err != error.FileNotFound) {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to load issues\") catch {};\n                store.deinit();\n                allocator.free(issues_path);\n                return CommandError.StorageError;\n            }\n        };\n\n        return CommandContext{\n            .allocator = allocator,\n            .output = output,\n            .store = store,\n            .issues_path = issues_path,\n            .global = global,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Clean up resources.\n    pub fn deinit(self: *CommandContext) void {\n        self.store.deinit();\n        self.allocator.free(self.issues_path);\n    }\n\n    /// Save the store to file if auto-flush is enabled.\n    pub fn saveIfAutoFlush(self: *CommandContext) CommandError!void {\n        if (!self.global.no_auto_flush) {\n            self.store.saveToFile() catch {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&self.output, self.global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to save issues\") catch {};\n                return CommandError.StorageError;\n            };\n        }\n    }\n\n    /// Create a dependency graph from the store.\n    pub fn createGraph(self: *CommandContext) DependencyGraph {\n        return DependencyGraph.init(&self.store, self.allocator);\n    }\n};\n\n/// Output a generic error message in the appropriate format.\npub fn outputErrorGeneric(output: *Output, json_mode: bool, message: []const u8) !void {\n    if (json_mode) {\n        try output.printJson(.{\n            .success = false,\n            .message = message,\n        });\n    } else {\n        try output.err(\"{s}\", .{message});\n    }\n}\n\n/// Output an error with a specific result type for JSON mode.\npub fn outputErrorTyped(\n    comptime T: type,\n    output: *Output,\n    json_mode: bool,\n    message: []const u8,\n) !void {\n    if (json_mode) {\n        const result = T{ .success = false, .message = message };\n        try output.printJson(result);\n    } else {\n        try output.err(\"{s}\", .{message});\n    }\n}\n\n/// Output a \"not found\" error for an issue.\npub fn outputNotFoundError(\n    comptime T: type,\n    output: *Output,\n    json_mode: bool,\n    id: []const u8,\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n) !void {\n    const msg = try std.fmt.allocPrint(allocator, \"issue not found: {s}\", .{id});\n    defer allocator.free(msg);\n    try outputErrorTyped(T, output, json_mode, msg);\n}\n\n/// Initialize just the output without loading workspace.\n/// Useful for commands that do their own workspace handling.\npub fn initOutput(allocator: std.mem.Allocator, global: args.GlobalOptions) Output {\n    return Output.init(allocator, .{\n        .json = global.json,\n        .toon = global.toon,\n        .quiet = global.quiet,\n        .silent = global.silent,\n        .no_color = global.no_color,\n    });\n}\n\n// --- Tests ---\n\ntest \"CommandContext returns null for uninitialized workspace\" {\n    const allocator = std.testing.allocator;\n    const global = args.GlobalOptions{ .silent = true, .data_path = \"/nonexistent/path\" };\n\n    const ctx = try CommandContext.init(allocator, global);\n    try std.testing.expect(ctx == null);\n}\n","numLines":164,"startLine":1,"totalLines":164}}}

Common CLI utilities shared across commands.\n//!\n//! Provides workspace loading, error handling, and shared result types\n//! to reduce duplication across command implementations.\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\nconst storage = @import(\"../storage/mod.zig\");\nconst output_mod = @import(\"../output/mod.zig\");\nconst args = @import(\"args.zig\");\n\npub const Output = output_mod.Output;\npub const OutputOptions = output_mod.OutputOptions;\npub const IssueStore = storage.IssueStore;\npub const DependencyGraph = storage.DependencyGraph;\n\n/// Common errors shared across CLI commands.\npub const CommandError = error{\n    WorkspaceNotInitialized,\n    StorageError,\n    OutOfMemory,\n};\n\n/// Context for executing a CLI command with an initialized workspace.\npub const CommandContext = struct {\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n    output: Output,\n    store: IssueStore,\n    issues_path: []const u8,\n    global: args.GlobalOptions,\n\n    /// Initialize a command context by loading the workspace.\n    /// Returns null and outputs an error if workspace is not initialized.\n    pub fn init(\n        allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n        global: args.GlobalOptions,\n    ) CommandError!?CommandContext {\n        var output = Output.init(allocator, .{\n            .json = global.json,\n            .toon = global.toon,\n            .quiet = global.quiet,\n            .silent = global.silent,\n            .no_color = global.no_color,\n        });\n\n        const beads_dir = global.data_path orelse \".beads\";\n        const issues_path = std.fs.path.join(allocator, &.{ beads_dir, \"issues.jsonl\" }) catch {\n            return CommandError.OutOfMemory;\n        };\n\n        std.fs.cwd().access(issues_path, .{}) catch |err| {\n            if (err == error.FileNotFound) {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"workspace not initialized. Run 'bz init' first.\") catch {};\n                allocator.free(issues_path);\n                return null;\n            }\n            outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"cannot access workspace\") catch {};\n            allocator.free(issues_path);\n            return CommandError.StorageError;\n        };\n\n        var store = IssueStore.init(allocator, issues_path);\n\n        store.loadFromFile() catch |err| {\n            if (err != error.FileNotFound) {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to load issues\") catch {};\n                store.deinit();\n                allocator.free(issues_path);\n                return CommandError.StorageError;\n            }\n        };\n\n        return CommandContext{\n            .allocator = allocator,\n            .output = output,\n            .store = store,\n            .issues_path = issues_path,\n            .global = global,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Clean up resources.\n    pub fn deinit(self: *CommandContext) void {\n        self.store.deinit();\n        self.allocator.free(self.issues_path);\n    }\n\n    /// Save the store to file if auto-flush is enabled.\n    pub fn saveIfAutoFlush(self: *CommandContext) CommandError!void {\n        if (!self.global.no_auto_flush) {\n            self.store.saveToFile() catch {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&self.output, self.global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to save issues\") catch {};\n                return CommandError.StorageError;\n            };\n        }\n    }\n\n    /// Create a dependency graph from the store.\n    pub fn createGraph(self: *CommandContext) DependencyGraph {\n        return DependencyGraph.init(&self.store, self.allocator);\n    }\n};\n\n/// Output a generic error message in the appropriate format.\npub fn outputErrorGeneric(output: *Output, json_mode: bool, message: []const u8) !void {\n    if (json_mode) {\n        try output.printJson(.{\n            .success = false,\n            .message = message,\n        });\n    } else {\n        try output.err(\"{s}\", .{message});\n    }\n}\n\n/// Output an error with a specific result type for JSON mode.\npub fn outputErrorTyped(\n    comptime T: type,\n    output: *Output,\n    json_mode: bool,\n    message: []const u8,\n) !void {\n    if (json_mode) {\n        const result = T{ .success = false, .message = message };\n        try output.printJson(result);\n    } else {\n        try output.err(\"{s}\", .{message});\n    }\n}\n\n/// Output a \"not found\" error for an issue.\npub fn outputNotFoundError(\n    comptime T: type,\n    output: *Output,\n    json_mode: bool,\n    id: []const u8,\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n) !void {\n    const msg = try std.fmt.allocPrint(allocator, \"issue not found: {s}\", .{id});\n    defer allocator.free(msg);\n    try outputErrorTyped(T, output, json_mode, msg);\n}\n\n/// Initialize just the output without });\n}\n\n// --- Tests ---\n\ntest \"CommandContext returns null for uninitialized workspace\" {\n    const allocator = std.testing.allocator;\n    const global = args.GlobalOptions{ .silent = true, Common CLI utilities shared across commands.\n//!\n//! Provides workspace loading, error handling, and shared result types\n//! to reduce duplication across command implementations.\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\nconst storage = @import(\"../storage/mod.zig\");\nconst output_mod = @import(\"../output/mod.zig\");\nconst args = @import(\"args.zig\");\n\npub const Output = output_mod.Output;\npub const OutputOptions = output_mod.OutputOptions;\npub const IssueStore = storage.IssueStore;\npub const DependencyGraph = storage.DependencyGraph;\npub const EventStore = storage.EventStore;\n\n/// Common errors shared across CLI commands.\npub const CommandError = error{\n    WorkspaceNotInitialized,\n    StorageError,\n    OutOfMemory,\n};\n\n/// Context for executing a CLI command with an initialized workspace.\npub const CommandContext = struct {\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n    output: Output,\n    store: IssueStore,\n    issues_path: []const u8,\n    global: args.GlobalOptions,\n\n    /// Initialize a command context by loading the workspace.\n    /// Returns null and outputs an error if workspace is not initialized.\n    pub fn init(\n        allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n        global: args.GlobalOptions,\n    ) CommandError!?CommandContext {\n        var output = Output.init(allocator, .{\n            .json = global.json,\n            .toon = global.toon,\n            .quiet = global.quiet,\n            .silent = global.silent,\n            .no_color = global.no_color,\n        });\n\n        const beads_dir = global.data_path orelse \".beads\";\n        const issues_path = std.fs.path.join(allocator, &.{ beads_dir, \"issues.jsonl\" }) catch {\n            return CommandError.OutOfMemory;\n        };\n\n        std.fs.cwd().access(issues_path, .{}) catch |err| {\n            if (err == error.FileNotFound) {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"workspace not initialized. Run 'bz init' first.\") catch {};\n                allocator.free(issues_path);\n                return null;\n            }\n            outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"cannot access workspace\") catch {};\n            allocator.free(issues_path);\n            return CommandError.StorageError;\n        };\n\n        var store = IssueStore.init(allocator, issues_path);\n\n        store.loadFromFile() catch |err| {\n            if (err != error.FileNotFound) {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to load issues\") catch {};\n                store.deinit();\n                allocator.free(issues_path);\n                return CommandError.StorageError;\n            }\n        };\n\n        return CommandContext{\n            .allocator = allocator,\n            .output = output,\n            .store = store,\n            .issues_path = issues_path,\n            .global = global,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Clean up resources.\n    pub fn deinit(self: *CommandContext) void {\n        self.store.deinit();\n        self.allocator.free(self.issues_path);\n    }\n\n    /// Save the store to file if auto-flush is enabled.\n    pub fn saveIfAutoFlush(self: *CommandContext) CommandError!void {\n        if (!self.global.no_auto_flush) {\n            self.store.saveToFile() catch {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&self.output, self.global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to save issues\") catch {};\n                return CommandError.StorageError;\n            };\n        }\n    }\n\n    /// Create a dependency graph from the store.\n    pub fn createGraph(self: *CommandContext) DependencyGraph {\n        return DependencyGraph.init(&self.store, self.allocator);\n    }\n};\n\n/// Output a generic error message in the appropriate format.\npub fn outputErrorGeneric(output: *Output, json_mode: bool, message: []const u8) !void {\n    if (json_mode) {\n        try output.printJson(.{\n            .success = false,\n            .message = message,\n        });\n    } else {\n        try output.err(\"{s}\", .{message});\n    }\n}\n\n/// Output an error with a specific result type for JSON mode.\npub fn outputErrorTyped(\n    comptime T: type,\n    output: *Output,\n    json_mode: bool,\n    message: []const u8,\n) !void {\n    if (json_mode) {\n        const result = T{ .success = false, .message = message };\n        try output.printJson(result);\n    } else {\n        try output.err(\"{s}\", .{message});\n    }\n}\n\n/// Output a \"not found\" error for an issue.\npub fn outputNotFoundError(\n    comptime T: type,\n    output: *Output,\n    json_mode: bool,\n    id: []const u8,\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n) !void {\n    const msg = try std.fmt.allocPrint(allocator, \"issue not found: {s}\", .{id});\n    defer allocator.free(msg);\n    try outputErrorTyped(T, output, json_mode, msg);\n}\n\n/// Initialize just the output without loading workspace.\n/// Useful for commands that do their own workspace handling.\npub fn initOutput(allocator: std.mem.Allocator, global: args.GlobalOptions) Output {\n    return Output.init(allocator, .{\n        .json = global.json,\n        .toon = global.toon,\n        .quiet = global.quiet,\n        .silent = global.silent,\n        .no_color = global.no_color,\n    });\n}\n\n// --- Tests ---\n\ntest \"CommandContext returns null for uninitialized workspace\" {\n    const allocator = std.testing.allocator;\n    const global = args.GlobalOptions{ .silent = true, Run 'bz init' first.\") catch {};\n                allocator.free(issues_path);\n                return null;\n            }\n            outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(),  }\n\n    /// Clean up resources.\n    pub fn deinit(self: *CommandContext) void {\n        self.store.deinit();\n        self.allocator.free(self.issues_path);\n    }\n\n    /// Save the store to self.allocator.free(self.issues_path);\n    }\n\n    /// Save the store to file if auto-flush is enabled.\n    pub fn saveIfAutoFlush(self: *CommandContext) CommandError!void {\n        if Provides workspace loading, error handling, and shared result types\n//! to reduce duplication across command implementations.\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\nconst storage = @import(\"../storage/mod.zig\");\nconst output_mod = @import(\"../output/mod.zig\");\nconst args = @import(\"args.zig\");\n\npub const Output = output_mod.Output;\npub const OutputOptions = output_mod.OutputOptions;\npub const IssueStore = storage.IssueStore;\npub const DependencyGraph = storage.DependencyGraph;\npub const EventStore = storage.EventStore;\n\n/// Common errors shared across CLI commands.\npub const CommandError = error{\n    WorkspaceNotInitialized,\n    StorageError,\n    OutOfMemory,\n};\n\n/// Context for executing a CLI command with an initialized workspace.\npub const CommandContext = struct {\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n    output: Output,\n    store: IssueStore,\n    event_store: EventStore,\n    issues_path: []const u8,\n    events_path: []const u8,\n    global: args.GlobalOptions,\n\n    /// Initialize a command context by loading the workspace.\n    /// Returns null and outputs an error if workspace is not initialized.\n    pub fn init(\n        allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n        global: args.GlobalOptions,\n    ) CommandError!?CommandContext {\n        var output = Output.init(allocator, .{\n            .json = global.json,\n            .toon = global.toon,\n            .quiet = global.quiet,\n            .silent = global.silent,\n            .no_color = global.no_color,\n        });\n\n        const beads_dir = global.data_path orelse \".beads\";\n        const issues_path = std.fs.path.join(allocator, &.{ beads_dir, \"issues.jsonl\" }) catch {\n            return CommandError.OutOfMemory;\n        };\n        const events_path = std.fs.path.join(allocator, &.{ beads_dir, \"events.jsonl\" }) catch {\n            allocator.free(issues_path);\n            return CommandError.OutOfMemory;\n        };\n\n        std.fs.cwd().access(issues_path, .{}) catch |err| {\n            if (err == error.FileNotFound) {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"workspace not initialized. Run 'bz init' first.\") catch {};\n                allocator.free(issues_path);\n                allocator.free(events_path);\n                return null;\n            }\n            outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"cannot access workspace\") catch {};\n            allocator.free(issues_path);\n            allocator.free(events_path);\n            return CommandError.StorageError;\n        };\n\n        var store = IssueStore.init(allocator, issues_path);\n\n        store.loadFromFile() catch |err| {\n            if (err != error.FileNotFound) {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to load issues\") catch {};\n                store.deinit();\n                allocator.free(issues_path);\n                allocator.free(events_path);\n                return CommandError.StorageError;\n            }\n        };\n\n        // Initialize event store and load next ID\n        var event_store = EventStore.init(allocator, events_path);\n        event_store.loadNextId() catch {}; // OK if events file doesn't exist\n\n        return CommandContext{\n            .allocator = allocator,\n            .output = output,\n            .store = store,\n            .event_store = event_store,\n            .issues_path = issues_path,\n            .events_path = events_path,\n            .global = global,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Clean up resources.\n    pub fn deinit(self: *CommandContext) void {\n        self.store.deinit();\n        self.allocator.free(self.issues_path);\n        self.allocator.free(self.events_path);\n    }\n\n    /// Save the store to file if auto-flush is enabled.\n    pub fn saveIfAutoFlush(self: *CommandContext) CommandError!void {\n        if (!self.global.no_auto_flush) {\n            self.store.saveToFile() catch {\n                outputErrorGeneric(&self.output, self.global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to save issues\") catch {};\n                return CommandError.StorageError;\n            };\n        }\n    }\n\n    /// Create a dependency graph from the store.\n    pub fn createGraph(self: *CommandContext) DependencyGraph {\n        return DependencyGraph.init(&self.store, self.allocator);\n    }\n};\n\n/// Output a generic error message in the appropriate format.\npub fn outputErrorGeneric(output: *Output, json_mode: bool, message: []const u8) !void {\n    if (json_mode) {\n        try output.printJson(.{\n            .success = false,\n            .message = message,\n        });\n    } else {\n        try output.err(\"{s}\", .{message});\n    }\n}\n\n/// Output an error with a specific result type for JSON mode.\npub fn outputErrorTyped(\n    comptime T: type,\n    output: *Output,\n    json_mode: bool,\n    message: []const u8,\n) !void {\n    if (json_mode) {\n        const result = T{ .success = false, .message = message };\n        try output.printJson(result);\n    } else {\n        try output.err(\"{s}\", .{message});\n    }\n}\n\n/// Output a \"not found\" error for an issue.\npub fn outputNotFoundError(\n    comptime T: type,\n    output: *Output,\n    json_mode: bool,\n    id: []const u8,\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n) !void {\n    const msg = try std.fmt.allocPrint(allocator, \"issue not found: {s}\", .{id});\n    defer allocator.free(msg);\n    try outputErrorTyped(T, output, json_mode, msg);\n}\n\n/// Initialize just the output without loading workspace.\n/// Useful for commands that do their own workspace handling.\npub fn initOutput(allocator: std.mem.Allocator, global: args.GlobalOptions) Output {\n    return Output.init(allocator, .{\n        .json = global.json,\n        .toon = global.toon,\n        .quiet = allocator = std.testing.allocator;\n    const global = args.GlobalOptions{ .silent = true, .data_path = \"/nonexistent/path\" };\n\n    const ctx = try CommandContext.init(allocator, global);\n    try EventInfo = struct {\n        event_type: []const u8,\n        actor: []const u8,\n        old_value: ?[]const u8,\n        new_value: ?[]const u8,\n        created_at: i64,\n    };\n};\n\npub fn (global.isStructuredOutput()) {\n            try ctx.output.printJson(HistoryResult{\n                .success = false,\n                .id = id,\n                .message = \"issue not found\",\n            });\n        } else {\n            try ctx.output.err(\"issue not found: {s}\", .{id});\n        }\n        return HistoryError.IssueNotFound;\n    }\n\n    // Get issue to show basic history   .old_value = null,\n        .new_value = issue.title,\n        .created_at = issue.created_at.value,\n    });\n\n    // If closed, add closed event\n    if (issue.closed_at.value) |closed_ts| {\n        try events.append(allocator, .{\n            .event_type = \"closed\",\n            .actor = \"unknown\",\n            .old_value = null,\n            .new_value = issue.close_reason,\n            .created_at = closed_ts,\n        });\n    }\n\n    // If updated (updated_at != created_at)\n    if (issue.updated_at.value != issue.created_at.value) {\n        try events.append(allocator, .{\n            .event_type = \"updated\",\n            .actor = \"unknown\",\n            .old_value = null,\n            .new_value = null,\n            .created_at = issue.updated_at.value,\n        });\n InvalidIssueType,\n    WorkspaceNotInitialized,\n    StorageError,\n    OutOfMemory,\n};\n\npub const CreateResult = struct {\n    success: bool,\n    id: ?[]const u8 = null,\n    title: ?[]const u8 = {\n    var output = common.initOutput(allocator, global);\n    const structured_output = global.isStructuredOutput();\n\n    // Validate title\n    if (create_args.title.len == 0) {\n        try common.outputErrorTyped(CreateResult, &output, structured_output, \"title cannot be empty\");\n        return CreateError.EmptyTitle;\n    }\n    if (create_args.title.len > 500) {\n        try common.outputErrorTyped(CreateResult, &output, structured_output, \"title exceeds 500 character limit\");\n        return CreateError.TitleTooLong;\n    }\n\n    // Determine workspace path\n    const beads_dir = global.data_path orelse \".beads\";\n    const issues_path = try std.fs.path.join(allocator, &.{ beads_dir, \"issues.jsonl\" });\n    defer allocator.free(issues_path);\n\n    // Check if workspace is initialized\n    std.fs.cwd().access(issues_path, .{}) catch |err| {\n        if (err == error.FileNotFound) {\n            try common.outputErrorTyped(CreateResult, &output, structured_output, \"workspace not initialized. Run 'bz init' first.\");\n            return CreateError.WorkspaceNotInitialized;\n        }\n        try common.outputErrorTyped(CreateResult, &output, structured_output, \"cannot access workspace\");\n        return CreateError.StorageError;\n    };\n\n    // Load existing issues\n    var store = IssueStore.init(allocator, issues_path);\n    defer store.deinit();\n\n    store.loadFromFile() catch |err| {\n        if (err != error.FileNotFound) {\n            try common.outputErrorTyped(CreateResult, &output, structured_output, \"failed to load issues\");\n            return CreateError.StorageError;\n        }\n    };\n\n    // Parse optional fields\n    const priority = if (create_args.priority) |p|\n        Priority.fromString(p) catch {\n            try const issue_type = if (create_args.issue_type) |t|\n        IssueType.fromString(t)\n    else\n        .task;\n\n    // Parse due date if provided\n    const due_at: ?i64 = if (create_args.due) |due_str|\n        parseDateString(due_str)\n    else\n        null;\n\n    // Get actor (from flag, env, or default)\n    const actor = global.actor orelse getDefaultActor();\n\n    // Get config prefix (read from config.yaml or use default)\n    const prefix = try getConfigPrefix(allocator, beads_dir);\n    defer allocator.free(prefix);\n\n    // Generate ID\n    var generator = IdGenerator.init(prefix);\n    const issue_count = store.countTotal();\n    const issue_id = try generator.generate(allocator, issue_count);\n    defer allocator.free(issue_id);\n\n    // Create issue\n    const now = std.time.timestamp();\n    var issue = Issue.init(issue_id, create_args.title, now);\n    issue.description = create_args.description;\n    issue.priority = priority;\n    issue.issue_type = issue_type;\n    issue.assignee = create_args.assignee;\n    issue.created_by = actor;\n    issue.due_at = .{ .value = due_at };\n    issue.estimated_minutes = create_args.estimate;\n\n    // Insert into store\n    store.insert(issue) catch {\n        try common.outputErrorTyped(CreateResult, &output, structured_output, \"failed to create issue\");\n        return CreateError.StorageError;\n    };\n\n    // Add labels\n    for (create_args.labels) |label| {\n        store.addLabel(issue_id, label) catch {};\n    }\n\n    // Save to file (auto-flush)\n    if (!global.no_auto_flush) {\n        store.saveToFile() catch {\n            try common.outputErrorTyped(CreateResult, &output, structured_output, \"failed to save issues\");\n            return ts;\n    }\n\n    // Try YYYY-MM-DD format\n    if (date_str.len == 10 and date_str[4] == '-' and date_str[7] == '-') {\n        const year = std.fmt.parseInt(i32, date_str[0..4], 10) catch return global: args.GlobalOptions,\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n) !void {\n    var ctx = (try CommandContext.init(allocator, global)) orelse {\n        return CloseError.WorkspaceNotInitialized;\n    };\n    defer ctx.deinit();\n\n    const issue_ref = ctx.store.getRef(close_args.id) orelse {\n        try common.outputNotFoundError(CloseResult, &ctx.output, global.isStructuredOutput(), close_args.id, allocator);\n        return CloseError.IssueNotFound;\n    };\n\n    if (statusEql(issue_ref.status, .closed)) {\n        try common.outputErrorTyped(CloseResult, &ctx.output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"issue is already closed\");\n        return CloseError.AlreadyClosed;\n    }\n\n    const now = std.time.timestamp();\n    var updates = IssueStore.IssueUpdate{\n        .status = .closed,\n        .closed_at = now,\n    };\n\n    if (close_args.reason) |r| {\n        updates.close_reason = r;\n    }\n\n    ctx.store.update(close_args.id, updates, now) catch {\n        try common.outputErrorTyped(CloseResult, &ctx.output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to close issue\");\n        return CloseError.StorageError;\n    };\n\n    try ctx.saveIfAutoFlush();\n\n    try outputSuccess(&ctx.output, global, close_args.id, \"closed\", \"Closed issue {s}\");\n}\n\npub fn runReopen(\n    reopen_args: args.ReopenArgs,\n    global: args.GlobalOptions,\n    allocator: };\n\n    ctx.store.update(reopen_args.id, updates, now) catch {\n        try common.outputErrorTyped(CloseResult, &ctx.output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to reopen issue\");\n        return CloseError.StorageError;\n    };\n\n    try ctx.saveIfAutoFlush();\n\n    try outputSuccess(&ctx.output, global, reopen_args.id, \"reopened\", \"Reopened issue {s}\");\n}\n\nfn outputSuccess(\n global: args.GlobalOptions,\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n) !void {\n    var ctx = (try CommandContext.init(allocator, global)) orelse {\n        return CloseError.WorkspaceNotInitialized;\n    };\n    defer ctx.deinit();\n\n    const issue_ref = ctx.store.getRef(close_args.id) orelse {\n        try common.outputNotFoundError(CloseResult, &ctx.output, global.isStructuredOutput(), close_args.id, allocator);\n        return CloseError.IssueNotFound;\n    };\n\n    if (statusEql(issue_ref.status, .closed)) {\n        try common.outputErrorTyped(CloseResult, &ctx.output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"issue is already closed\");\n        return CloseError.AlreadyClosed;\n    }\n\n    const now = std.time.timestamp();\n    var updates = IssueStore.IssueUpdate{\n        .status = .closed,\n        .closed_at = now,\n    };\n\n    if (close_args.reason) |r| {\n        updates.close_reason = r;\n    }\n\n    ctx.store.update(close_args.id, updates, now) catch {\n        try common.outputErrorTyped(CloseResult, &ctx.output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to close issue\");\n        return CloseError.StorageError;\n    };\n\n    // Record audit event\n    const actor = global.actor orelse \"unknown\";\n    const event = Event.issueClosed(allocator, close_args.id, actor, close_args.reason, now) catch Event{\n        .id = 0,\n        .issue_id = close_args.id,\n        .event_type = .closed,\n        .actor = actor,\n        .old_value = null,\n        .new_value = close_args.reason,\n        .created_at = now,\n    };\n    ctx.recordEvent(event);\n\n    try ctx.saveIfAutoFlush();\n\n    try outputSuccess(&ctx.output, global, close_args.id, \"closed\", \"Closed issue {s}\");\n}\n\npub fn runReopen(\n    reopen_args: CloseError.WorkspaceNotInitialized;\n    };\n    defer ctx.deinit();\n\n    const issue_ref = ctx.store.getRef(reopen_args.id) orelse {\n        try common.outputNotFoundError(CloseResult, common.outputErrorTyped(CloseResult, &ctx.output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"issue is not closed\");\n        return CloseError.NotClosed;\n    }\n\n    const now = std.time.timestamp();\n    const updates = IssueStore.IssueUpdate{\n        .status = .open,\n        .closed_at = 0,\n    };\n\n    ctx.store.update(reopen_args.id, updates, now) catch {\n        try common.outputErrorTyped(CloseResult, &ctx.output, global.isStructuredOutput(), \"failed to reopen issue\");\n        return CloseError.StorageError;\n    };\n\n    try ctx.saveIfAutoFlush();\n\n    try outputSuccess(&ctx.output, global, reopen_args.id, \"reopened\", \"Reopened issue {s}\");\n}\n\nfn outputSuccess(\n    output: *common.Output,\n    global: args.GlobalOptions,\n    id: []const u8,\n    action: []const u8,\n    comptime fmt: []const u8,\n) !void {\n    if (global.isStructuredOutput()) {\n        try output.printJson(CloseResult{\n            .success = true,\n            .id = id,\n            .action = action,\n        });\n    } else if (global.quiet) {\n        try output.raw(id);\n        try output.raw(\"\\n\");\n    } else {\n        try output.success(fmt, .{id});\n    }\n}\n\nfn statusEql(a: Status, b: Status) bool {\n    const Tag = std.meta.Tag(Status);\n    const tag_a: Tag = a;\n    const tag_b: Tag = b;\n    if (tag_a != tag_b) return false;\n    if (tag_a == .custom) {\n        return std.mem.eql(u8, a.custom, b.custom);\n    }\n    return true;\n}\n\n// --- Tests ---\n\ntest \"CloseError enum exists\" {\n    const err: CloseError = .id = \"bd-abc123\",\n        .action = \"closed\",\n    };\n    try std.testing.expect(result.success);\n    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"bd-abc123\", result.id.?);\n    try (std.fs.path.dirname(self.wal_path)) |parent| {\n            dir.makePath(parent) catch |err| switch (err) {\n                error.PathAlreadyExists => {},\n                else => return err,\n Legacy format (plain JSON lines) is also supported for reading:\n//! {\"op\":\"add\",\"ts\":1706540000,\"id\":\"bd-abc123\",\"data\":{...}}\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\nconst fs = std.fs;\nconst Issue = @import(\"../models/issue.zig\").Issue;\nconst BeadsLock = @import(\"lock.zig\").BeadsLock;\nconst IssueStore = @import(\"store.zig\").IssueStore;\nconst test_util = @import(\"../test_util.zig\");\n\n/// Magic bytes to identify framed WAL entries: 0x000B3AD5 (\"BEADS\" in hex-ish)\npub const WAL_MAGIC: u32 = 0x000B3AD5;\n\n/// Size of the binary frame header (magic + crc + len)\npub const FRAME_HEADER_SIZE: usize = 12;\n\npub const WalError = error{\n    WalCorrupted,\n    WriteError,\n    LockFailed,\n    InvalidOperation,\n    ParseError,\n    OutOfMemory,\n    ReplayPartialFailure,\n    ChecksumMismatch,\n};","originalFile":"//! Write-Ahead Log (WAL) for beads_zig.\n//!\n//! Provides constant-time concurrent writes by appending operations to a WAL file\n//! rather than rewriting the entire main JSONL file. Operations are:\n//! - Serialized via flock before append\n//! - fsync'd before lock release for durability\n//! - Replayed on read to reconstruct current state\n//!\n//! WAL entry format (JSON lines):\n//! {\"op\":\"add\",\"ts\":1706540000,\"id\":\"bd-abc123\",\"data\":{...}}\n//! {\"op\":\"close\",\"ts\":1706540001,\"id\":\"bd-abc123\",\"data\":null}\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\nconst fs = std.fs;\nconst Issue = @import(\"../models/issue.zig\").Issue;\nconst BeadsLock = @import(\"lock.zig\").BeadsLock;\nconst IssueStore = @import(\"store.zig\").IssueStore;\nconst test_util = @import(\"../test_util.zig\");\n\npub const WalError = error{\n    WalCorrupted,\n    WriteError,\n    LockFailed,\n    InvalidOperation,\n    ParseError,\n    OutOfMemory,\n    ReplayPartialFailure,\n};\n\n/// Statistics from WAL replay operations.\npub const ReplayStats = struct {\n    applied: usize = 0,\n    skipped: usize = 0,\n    failed: usize = 0,\n    failure_ids: []const []const u8 = &.{},\n\n    pub fn deinit(self: *ReplayStats, allocator: std.mem.Allocator) void {\n        for (self.failure_ids) |id| {\n            allocator.free(id);\n        }\n        if (self.failure_ids.len > 0) {\n            allocator.free(self.failure_ids);\n        }\n    }\n\n    pub fn hasFailures(self: ReplayStats) bool {\n        return self.failed > 0;\n    }\n};\n\n/// WAL operation types.\npub const WalOp = enum {\n    add,\n    update,\n    close,\n    reopen,\n    delete,\n    set_blocked,\n    unset_blocked,\n\n    pub fn toString(self: WalOp) []const u8 {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .add => \"add\",\n            .update => \"update\",\n            .close => \"close\",\n            .reopen => \"reopen\",\n            .delete => \"delete\",\n            .set_blocked => \"set_blocked\",\n            .unset_blocked => \"unset_blocked\",\n        };\n    }\n\n    pub fn fromString(s: []const u8) ?WalOp {\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"add\")) return .add;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"update\")) return .update;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"close\")) return .close;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"reopen\")) return .reopen;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"delete\")) return .delete;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"set_blocked\")) return .set_blocked;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"unset_blocked\")) return .unset_blocked;\n        return null;\n    }\n};\n\n/// A single WAL entry representing one operation.\npub const WalEntry = struct {\n    op: WalOp,\n    ts: i64, // Unix timestamp for ordering\n    id: []const u8, // Issue ID\n    data: ?Issue, // Full issue for add/update, null for status-only ops\n\n    const Self = @This();\n\n    /// Custom JSON serialization for WalEntry.\n    pub fn jsonStringify(self: Self, jws: anytype) !void {\n        try jws.beginObject();\n\n        try jws.objectField(\"op\");\n        try jws.write(self.op.toString());\n\n        try jws.objectField(\"ts\");\n        try jws.write(self.ts);\n\n        try jws.objectField(\"id\");\n        try jws.write(self.id);\n\n        try jws.objectField(\"data\");\n        if (self.data) |issue| {\n            try jws.write(issue);\n        } else {\n            try jws.write(null);\n        }\n\n        try jws.endObject();\n    }\n};\n\n/// Parsed WAL entry for replay.\npub const ParsedWalEntry = struct {\n    op: WalOp,\n    ts: i64,\n    id: []const u8,\n    data: ?Issue,\n\n    pub fn deinit(self: *ParsedWalEntry, allocator: std.mem.Allocator) void {\n        allocator.free(self.id);\n        if (self.data) |*issue| {\n            var i = issue.*;\n            i.deinit(allocator);\n        }\n    }\n};\n\n/// WAL file manager for reading and writing operations.\npub const Wal = struct {\n    wal_path: []const u8,\n    lock_path: []const u8,\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n\n    const Self = @This();\n\n    pub fn init(beads_dir: []const u8, allocator: std.mem.Allocator) !Self {\n        const wal_path = try std.fs.path.join(allocator, &.{ beads_dir, \"beads.wal\" });\n        errdefer allocator.free(wal_path);\n\n        const lock_path = try std.fs.path.join(allocator, &.{ beads_dir, \"beads.lock\" });\n\n        return Self{\n            .wal_path = wal_path,\n            .lock_path = lock_path,\n            .allocator = allocator,\n        };\n    }\n\n    pub fn deinit(self: *Self) void {\n        self.allocator.free(self.wal_path);\n        self.allocator.free(self.lock_path);\n    }\n\n    /// Append an entry to the WAL under exclusive lock.\n    /// Ensures durability via fsync before releasing lock.\n    pub fn appendEntry(self: *Self, entry: WalEntry) !void {\n        var lock = BeadsLock.acquire(self.lock_path) catch return WalError.LockFailed;\n        defer lock.release();\n\n        try self.appendEntryUnlocked(entry);\n    }\n\n    /// Append entry without acquiring lock (caller must hold lock).\n    fn appendEntryUnlocked(self: *Self, entry: WalEntry) !void {\n        const dir = fs.cwd();\n\n        // Ensure parent directory exists\n        if (std.fs.path.dirname(self.wal_path)) |parent| {\n            dir.makePath(parent) catch |err| switch (err) {\n                error.PathAlreadyExists => {},\n                else => return err,\n            };\n        }\n\n        // Open or create WAL file in append mode\n        const file = dir.createFile(self.wal_path, .{\n            .truncate = false,\n        }) catch return WalError.WriteError;\n        defer file.close();\n\n        // Seek to end\n        file.seekFromEnd(0) catch return WalError.WriteError;\n\n        // Serialize entry\n        const json_bytes = std.json.Stringify.valueAlloc(self.allocator, entry, .{}) catch return WalError.WriteError;\n        defer self.allocator.free(json_bytes);\n\n        // Write entry + newline\n        file.writeAll(json_bytes) catch return WalError.WriteError;\n        file.writeAll(\"\\n\") catch return WalError.WriteError;\n\n        // fsync for durability\n        file.sync() catch return WalError.WriteError;\n    }\n\n    /// Read all WAL entries.\n    pub fn readEntries(self: *Self) ![]ParsedWalEntry {\n        const file = fs.cwd().openFile(self.wal_path, .{}) catch |err| switch (err) {\n            error.FileNotFound => return &[_]ParsedWalEntry{},\n            else => return err,\n        };\n        defer file.close();\n\n        const content = file.readToEndAlloc(self.allocator, 100 * 1024 * 1024) catch return WalError.ParseError;\n        defer self.allocator.free(content);\n\n        var entries: std.ArrayListUnmanaged(ParsedWalEntry) = .{};\n        errdefer {\n            for (entries.items) |*e| {\n                e.deinit(self.allocator);\n            }\n            entries.deinit(self.allocator);\n        }\n\n        var line_start: usize = 0;\n        for (content, 0..) |c, i| {\n            if (c == '\\n') {\n                const line = content[line_start..i];\n                line_start = i + 1;\n\n                if (line.len == 0) continue;\n\n                if (self.parseEntry(line)) |entry| {\n                    try entries.append(self.allocator, entry);\n                } else |_| {\n                    // Skip malformed entries (graceful degradation)\n                    continue;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        // Handle last line if no trailing newline\n        if (line_start < content.len) {\n            const line = content[line_start..];\n            if (line.len > 0) {\n                if (self.parseEntry(line)) |entry| {\n                    try entries.append(self.allocator, entry);\n                } else |_| {}\n            }\n        }\n\n        return entries.toOwnedSlice(self.allocator);\n    }\n\n    /// Parse a single WAL entry line.\n    fn parseEntry(self: *Self, line: []const u8) !ParsedWalEntry {\n        const parsed = std.json.parseFromSlice(\n            struct {\n                op: []const u8,\n                ts: i64,\n                id: []const u8,\n                data: ?Issue,\n            },\n            self.allocator,\n            line,\n            .{ .ignore_unknown_fields = true, .allocate = .alloc_always },\n        ) catch return WalError.ParseError;\n        defer parsed.deinit();\n\n        const op = WalOp.fromString(parsed.value.op) orelse return WalError.InvalidOperation;\n\n        // Clone strings since parsed will be freed\n        const id = try self.allocator.dupe(u8, parsed.value.id);\n        errdefer self.allocator.free(id);\n\n        var data: ?Issue = null;\n        if (parsed.value.data) |issue| {\n            data = try issue.clone(self.allocator);\n        }\n\n        return ParsedWalEntry{\n            .op = op,\n            .ts = parsed.value.ts,\n            .id = id,\n            .data = data,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Replay WAL entries onto an IssueStore.\n    /// Applies operations in timestamp order.\n    /// Returns statistics about the replay including any failures.\n    pub fn replay(self: *Self, store: *IssueStore) !ReplayStats {\n        const entries = try self.readEntries();\n        defer {\n            for (entries) |*e| {\n                var entry = e.*;\n                entry.deinit(self.allocator);\n            }\n            self.allocator.free(entries);\n        }\n\n        // Sort by timestamp (sortUnstable mutates through the slice pointer)\n        std.mem.sortUnstable(ParsedWalEntry, @constCast(entries), {}, struct {\n            fn lessThan(_: void, a: ParsedWalEntry, b: ParsedWalEntry) bool {\n                return a.ts < b.ts;\n            }\n        }.lessThan);\n\n        // Track replay results\n        var stats = ReplayStats{};\n        var failure_ids: std.ArrayListUnmanaged([]const u8) = .{};\n        errdefer {\n            for (failure_ids.items) |id| {\n                self.allocator.free(id);\n            }\n            failure_ids.deinit(self.allocator);\n        }\n\n        // Apply each operation\n        for (entries) |entry| {\n            const result = self.applyEntry(store, entry);\n            switch (result) {\n                .applied => stats.applied += 1,\n                .skipped => stats.skipped += 1,\n                .failed => {\n                    stats.failed += 1;\n                    const id_copy = self.allocator.dupe(u8, entry.id) catch continue;\n                    failure_ids.append(self.allocator, id_copy) catch {\n                        self.allocator.free(id_copy);\n                    };\n                },\n            }\n        }\n\n        stats.failure_ids = failure_ids.toOwnedSlice(self.allocator) catch &.{};\n        return stats;\n    }\n\n    /// Result of applying a single WAL entry.\n    const ApplyResult = enum {\n        applied,\n        skipped,\n        failed,\n    };\n\n    /// Apply a single WAL entry to the store.\n    /// Returns the result of the operation.\n    fn applyEntry(self: *Self, store: *IssueStore, entry: ParsedWalEntry) ApplyResult {\n        _ = self;\n        switch (entry.op) {\n            .add => {\n                if (entry.data) |issue| {\n                    // Only insert if not already present\n                    if (!store.id_index.contains(issue.id)) {\n                        store.insert(issue) catch |err| switch (err) {\n                            error.DuplicateId => return .skipped, // Already exists\n                            else => return .failed,\n                        };\n                        return .applied;\n                    }\n                    return .skipped; // Already exists\n                }\n                return .skipped; // No data for add op\n            },\n            .update => {\n                if (entry.data) |issue| {\n                    // Update or insert\n                    if (store.id_index.contains(issue.id)) {\n                        // Full replacement for simplicity\n                        const idx = (magic + crc + len)\npub const FRAME_HEADER_SIZE: usize = 12;\n\npub const WalError = error{\n    WalCorrupted,\n    WriteError,\n    LockFailed,\n    InvalidOperation,\n    ParseError,\n allocator.free(id);\n        }\n        if (self.failure_ids.len > 0) {\n            allocator.free(self.failure_ids);\n        }\n    }\n\n    pub fn hasFailures(self: ReplayStats) bool {\n        return self.failed > 0;\n    }\n};\n\n/// WAL operation types.\npub const WalOp = enum {\n    add,\n    update,\n    close,\n    reopen,\n    delete,\n    set_blocked,\n    unset_blocked,\n\n    pub fn toString(self: WalOp) []const u8 {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .add => \"add\",\n            .update => \"update\",\n            .close => \"close\",\n            .reopen => \"reopen\",\n            .delete => \"delete\",\n            .set_blocked => \"set_blocked\",\n            .unset_blocked => \"unset_blocked\",\n        };\n    }\n\n    pub fn fromString(s: []const u8) ?WalOp {\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"add\")) return .add;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"update\")) return .update;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"close\")) return .close;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"reopen\")) return .reopen;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"delete\")) return .delete;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"set_blocked\")) return .set_blocked;\n        if (std.mem.eql(u8, s, \"unset_blocked\")) return .unset_blocked;\n        return null;\n    }\n};\n\n/// A single WAL entry representing one operation.\npub const WalEntry = struct {\n    op: WalOp,\n    ts: i64, // Unix timestamp for ordering\n    id: []const u8, // Issue ID\n    data: ?Issue, // Full issue for add/update, null for status-only ops\n\n    const Self = @This();\n\n    /// Custom JSON }\n};\n\n/// Parsed WAL entry for replay.\npub const ParsedWalEntry = struct {\n    op: WalOp,\n    ts: i64,\n    id: []const u8,\n    data: ?Issue,\n\n    pub fn deinit(self: *ParsedWalEntry, allocator: std.mem.Allocator) void {\n        allocator.free(self.id);\n        if (self.data) |*issue| {\n            var i = issue.*;\n            i.deinit(allocator);\n        }\n    }\n};\n\n/// allocator.free(id);\n        }\n        if (self.failure_ids.len > 0) {\n            allocator.free(self.failure_ids);\n        }\n    }\n\n    pub fn hasFailures(self: ReplayStats) bool {\n        return self.failed > 0;\n    }\n};\n\n/// WAL operation types.\npub const WalOp = enum {\n    add,\n    update,\n    close,\n    reopen,\n    delete,\n    set_blocked,\n    unset_blocked,\n\n    pub
